{"name":"Lake.DSL.Package","instances":[],"imports":["Init","Lake.Config.Package","Lake.DSL.Attributes","Lake.DSL.DeclUtil"],"declarations":[{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b614ff1d12bc38f39077f9ce9f2d48b42c003ad0/src/lake/Lake/DSL/Package.lean#L41-L65","name":"Lake.DSL.postUpdateDecl","line":41,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Lake/DSL/Package.html#Lake.DSL.postUpdateDecl","doc":"Declare a post-`lake update` hook for the package.\nRuns the monadic action is after a successful `lake update` execution\nin this package or one of its downstream dependents.\n\n**Example**\n\nThis feature enables Mathlib to synchronize the Lean toolchain and run\n`cache get` after a `lake update`:\n\n```\nlean_exe cache\npost_update pkg do\n  let wsToolchainFile := (← getRootPackage).dir / \"lean-toolchain\"\n  let mathlibToolchain ← IO.FS.readFile <| pkg.dir / \"lean-toolchain\"\n  IO.FS.writeFile wsToolchainFile mathlibToolchain\n  let exeFile ← runBuild cache.build >>= (·.await)\n  let exitCode ← env exeFile.toString #[\"get\"]\n  if exitCode ≠ 0 then\n    error s!\"{pkg.name}: failed to fetch cache\"\n```\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lake/DSL/Package.html#Lake.DSL.postUpdateDecl\"><span class=\"name\">Lake</span>.<span class=\"name\">DSL</span>.<span class=\"name\">postUpdateDecl</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">Lean.ParserDescr</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b614ff1d12bc38f39077f9ce9f2d48b42c003ad0/src/lake/Lake/DSL/Package.lean#L32-L38","name":"Lake.DSL.packageDecl","line":32,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Lake/DSL/Package.html#Lake.DSL.packageDecl","doc":"Defines the configuration of a Lake package.  Has many forms:\n\n```lean\npackage «pkg-name»\npackage «pkg-name» { /- config opts -/ }\npackage «pkg-name» where /- config opts -/\n```\n\nThere can only be one `package` declaration per Lake configuration file.\nThe defined package configuration will be available for reference as `_package`.\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lake/DSL/Package.html#Lake.DSL.packageDecl\"><span class=\"name\">Lake</span>.<span class=\"name\">DSL</span>.<span class=\"name\">packageDecl</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">Lean.ParserDescr</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b614ff1d12bc38f39077f9ce9f2d48b42c003ad0/src/lake/Lake/DSL/Package.lean#L18-L18","name":"Lake.DSL.packageDeclName","line":18,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Lake/DSL/Package.html#Lake.DSL.packageDeclName","doc":"The name given to the definition created by the `package` syntax. "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lake/DSL/Package.html#Lake.DSL.packageDeclName\"><span class=\"name\">Lake</span>.<span class=\"name\">DSL</span>.<span class=\"name\">packageDeclName</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Name\">Lake.Name</a></div></div>"}]}